## Group exercise - Evaluation

1. Create a file in this folder
2. Copy the requirements below into it
3. Tick the right boxes
4. Commit/push the change
---

## Requirements

### Perfection is not a detail
- [ ] All buttons and links work
  - Links in footer don't work or lead to unexpected result (adress goes to website of the beacon in stead of google maps).
- [ ] All elements work and are complete (menu, lists, images, ...)
  - Pictures don't show in Safari browser.
  - "Strap on your Eagle pack" picture is not transparent.
  - Links don't have titles
- [ ] Everything on the page has a function, a reason to be there
  - the 4 pictures of the jetpack speeders show the names of the teammembers, but why is that shown there?
- [ ] No dead links
  - "Location" link in footer leads to nowhere. 
  - "How it works" link (on the page, not in the menu) doesn't work. 
- [x] English and dutch are not mixed
- [ ] No spelling errors
  - "Safety": we strive to make te best jetpacks...
  - "Tech": sollidstate batterys...
- [x] No grammar errors
- [x] The website is deployed somewhere
- [x] Everything is relevant (no image of a barber on the website of a baker)

### Content
- [x] Openinghours (if needed)
  - No openinghours but not needes because locations all over the world. 
- [x] Address (if needed)
- [x] Google maps
- [x] Clickable email
- [ ] A working form (you can use https://formspree.io)
  - Email button is not activated.


### Text life matters aka typography is real
- [x] Some words are bolded
- [ ] Some words are italic
- [x] Some words have a different color
- [x] We aren't using a default font, cause it's not 2004
- [x] Contrast is not too low
- [ ] Typographic hierachy is correct
  - H1, H5, H3,... are used a bit chaotically.
- [ ] Text has a clear intro, middle, conclusion
  - We miss the intro, which is very clear in the readme but not found on the website. 
- [x] Intro, middle, conclusion is style correctly
- [x] Headline font is a headline font
- [x] Body text font is a body text font
- [x] The text on the page has a good flow

### Style
- [x] Black is almost black but not #000
- [ ] White is almost white but not #fff
  - #fff is used on certain elements.
- [ ] The website is not an ugly color mess
  - We don't really like the colors (the green, purple and dark locations are a bit much). 
- [x] The styling is consistent
- [ ] It is not four totally different pages thrown together
  - It actually does look a little thrown together.
- [x] Everything works even if you are colorblind
  - There is no padding on the question box element


### Not everyone has free 4G aka speed matters
- [x] Pictures are not too heavy
- [x] Pictures are not pixelated

### A company wants to be found/SEO	
- [x] All the keywords this company wants to be found on are on the page  
  - which are the keywords this company want to be found with? These are not in the 'keywords' meta tag but we think they are 'jetpack, fly, eagle,...' and these are all on the page. 
- [x] Page has an H1 tag
- [ ] Page has keyword meta tags
  - Keywords meta tags is there but contains wrong sort of words (css, html, js,...) --> jetpack, fly, eagle, ...
- [x] Page has a title with the keywords in
- [x] Page loads fast
 
### Keep your workspace clean
- [ ] No unused files in the repo
  - All html files could be grouped in the 1 index.html.
- [x] All files have a good, clear name
- [x] Good folder structure
  - IlgerCSS + CSS?
- [x] The CSS folder does not have an image folder
- [ ] Not too many files in the root folder 
  - Too many html files. 

### Git(hub) is what you make it
- [x] All commits use the correct format (if applied this commit will...)
- [x] A github description has been filled in
- [x] A github website has been filled in
- [ ] Github topics have been filled in

### Readme but also writeme
- [x] No license text in the readme, put it in a seperate file
- [x] But a license is defined
- [x] And it is included in the readme by name or a quick summary
- [x] The readme says who made it
- [x] The readme says why they made it
- [x] The readme explains what this repo/project is
- [ ] The readme explains why it is on github
- [x] The readme links to the preview
- [x] The readme contains a nice image
- [x] The readme does not contain the readme/license of dependencies, libraries, templates
- [x] If needed they are included in the repo and are mentioned in the readme
- [x] The readme has a markdown title
- [x] The readme is divided in sections
- [x] The readme is fun to read
- [x] The readme looks good
- [x] The readme is clear, even for someone that has no idea what is going on

### I'm So Meta, Even This Acronym
- [ ] Social media sharing meta tags are correct
- [x] Keywords meta tag
- [x] Description meta tag
- [x] Title of the page is included
- [ ] Favicon is included
- [x] Responsive meta tag is included
- [x] Charset is defined
- [x] Author is defined

### Data is the new oil
- [x] (Google) analytics

### Perform all the tests
- [ ] Lighthouse
- [ ] W3C validator
- [ ] Monkey test

### Putting the antics back in semantics (but only for the html)
- [x] The html is semanticly correct
  - <p> elements are used for every seperate sentance, while you could use just 1 <p> element and insert </br> for breaks.
- [x] Navigation is in a nav
- [x] Lists use list tags
- [x] H tags are used to signal importance
- [ ] No div is used where another element is available
- [ ] No span is used where another element is available
- [x] No inline styling is put on any element
- [x] Id's are only used once
- [x] The same 'type' of elements have the same classes
- [ ] All images have an alt attribute and a title


### Just kidding CSS deserves some love too
- [ ] CSS follows the DRY principle
  - There are 3 parallax classes used, perhaps they could be defined in the same way in css so they have a consistent look and feel on the webpage? 
- [x] The CSS does not contain conflicting selectors (multiple definition for the same class/id)
- [x] There is no use of !important where it can be avoided
- [ ] The page is responsive
  - The google maps element disturbs the smartphone view. 


### Thermometer goes WHERE???
- [ ] Your own style is included after the style of frameworks
  - Only Bulma colors and typography used. 
- [x] Script tags are put at the end of the body or in the head with async/defer if possible


### Errors are to be avoided
- [x] No http resources are used on an https website
- [ ] The console shows no errors
  - In Chrome, the console shows 3 errors. 

